With chart js how to configure it to not display duplicated tick on the x axis

To prevent duplicate ticks on the x-axis in Chart.js, you can add a custom `callback` function to the x-axis ticks configuration that filters out duplicate values. Here's the patch to implement this:

<patch>
<title>Prevent duplicate x-axis ticks in chart</title>
<edit>
<path>app/src/app/components/shared/graph/VisualizationGraph.jsx</path>
<description>Add callback function to x-axis ticks to filter duplicates</description>
<operation>update</operation>
<old_text>
      config.options.scales.x = {
        offset: true,
        type: 'category',
        grid: {
          display: false,
        },
        ticks: {
          padding: 10,
        },
      };
</old_text>
<new_text>
      config.options.scales.x = {
        offset: true,
        type: 'category',
        grid: {
          display: false,
        },
        ticks: {
          padding: 10,
          callback: function(value, index, ticks) {
            // Return value only if it's the first occurrence or different from previous tick
            if (index === 0 || value !== ticks[index - 1].value) {
              return value;
            }
            return null; // Skip duplicate values
          }
        },
      };
</new_text>
</edit>
</patch>

This change adds a callback function to the x-axis ticks configuration that:
1. Returns the tick value if it's the first tick (index === 0)
2. Returns the tick value if it's different from the previous tick
3. Returns null for duplicate values, which Chart.js will skip when rendering

This ensures that only unique tick values are displayed on the x-axis, preventing duplicates while maintaining proper spacing and alignment.
